19/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Fires continued to ravage areas across Greece on Wednesday (August 19th). A new blaze is reported on the island of Zakynthos, in the Ionian Sea. Fires in Kalathenes, on Crete, are being contained. Fire fighters battled flames in the town of Thiva, in central Greece, for a second day Tuesday, prompting the evacuations of children and the elderly. Soaring temperatures and strong winds are complicating the situation. (Zugla - 19/08/09; DPA, Reuters - 18/08/09)
